bgp:PeerEntry.label: BGP Peer Entry
comment: The BGP peer status specifies the status of a relationship between BGP speakers. A BGP speaker does not discover another BGP speaker automatically.  You must configure the relationships between BGP speakers. A BGP peer is a BGP speaker that has an active TCP connection to another BGP speaker.
Delete or ignore. For internal use only.
